snippet.title: TRAIL BLAZERS at LAKERS | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | August 29, 2020
snippet.description:
TRAIL BLAZERS at LAKERS | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | August 29, 2020

Led by LeBron James‚Äô 36 PTS, 10 REB and 10 AST, the Los Angeles Lakers defeated the Portland Trail Blazers, 131-122, in Game 5. Additionally for the Lakers, Anthony Davis tallied 43 PTS and 9 REB in the victory, while CJ McCollum paced the Trail Blazers with 36 PTS and 7 AST. The Lakers will now advance to the Western Conference Semifinals after closing out this best-of-seven series, 4-1. They will face the winner of the Houston Rockets-Oklahoma City Thunder series.

snippet.description:
damon‚Äôs channel ‚û≠ https://www.youtube.com/damondominique

A long overdue travel vlog from the good ol days when you could still travel, go to a warehouse rave, and make out with a stranger. During my 72 hours in Paris, I drank mimosas by the Seine, found out I've been calling chocolate croissants the wrong name my entire life, put together an outfit for a night out, danced (very badly), went to an art museum, drank tea in a bathtub, got stood up by a cutie in overalls, and spent way too much time gossiping about boys and Tinder/Grindr dates with my fellow hopeless romanic, Damon Dominique.

snippet.description:

snippet.description:
How would you know you‚Äôre being sexually harassed?

In this episode, the cast speak up about their unfortunate experience of being sexually harassed and give advice on what we should do if such a thing were to happen, not only to us, but to others as well.

If you have experienced any form of sexual harassment and are in need of help, please visit:

Sexual Assault Care Centre
http://sacc.aware.org.sg/

AWARE Singapore
https://www.aware.org.sg/

Subscribe for more content like this: http://bit.ly/SubscribeMOSG

snippet.title: The Batman - DC FanDome Teaser
snippet.description:
Robert Pattinson is #TheBatman.

https://www.instagram.com/thebatman/
https://www.facebook.com/thebatman
https://twitter.com/thebatman
http://thebatman.com

From Warner Bros. Pictures comes ‚ÄúThe Batman,‚Äù with director Matt Reeves (the ‚ÄúPlanet of the Apes‚Äù films) at the helm and with Robert Pattinson (‚ÄúTenet,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Lighthouse,‚Äù ‚ÄúGood Time‚Äù) starring as Gotham City‚Äôs vigilante detective, Batman, and billionaire Bruce Wayne.

Also in the star-studded ensemble as Gotham‚Äôs famous and infamous cast of characters are Zo√´ Kravitz (‚ÄúFantastic Beasts: The Crimes of Grindelwald,‚Äù ‚ÄúMad Max: Fury Road‚Äù) as Selina Kyle; Paul Dano (‚ÄúLove & Mercy,‚Äù ‚Äú12 Years a Slave‚Äù) as Edward Nashton; Jeffrey Wright (the ‚ÄúHunger Games‚Äù films) as the GCPD‚Äôs James Gordon; John Turturro (the ‚ÄúTransformers‚Äù films) as Carmine Falcone; Peter Sarsgaard (‚ÄúThe Magnificent Seven,‚Äù ‚ÄúBlack Mass‚Äù) as Gotham D.A. Gil Colson; Barry Keoghan (‚ÄúDunkirk‚Äù) as Officer Stanley Merkel; Jayme Lawson (‚ÄúFarewell Amor‚Äù) as mayoral candidate Bella Re√°l; with Andy Serkis (the ‚ÄúPlanet of the Apes‚Äù films, ‚ÄúBlack Panther‚Äù) as Alfred; and Colin Farrell (‚ÄúFantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them,‚Äù ‚ÄúDumbo‚Äù) as Oswald Cobblepot.

‚ÄúThe Batman‚Äù was written by Matt Reeves & Peter Craig.  Reeves and Dylan Clark (the ‚ÄúPlanet of the Apes‚Äù films) are producing the film, with Simon Emanuel, Michael E. Uslan, Walter Hamada and Chantal Nong Vo serving as executive producers.  Reeves‚Äô behind-the-scenes creative team includes Oscar-nominated director of photography Greig Fraser (‚ÄúLion,‚Äù upcoming ‚ÄúDune‚Äù); his ‚ÄúPlanet of the Apes‚Äù production designer, James Chinlund; editors William Hoy (the ‚ÄúPlanet of the Apes‚Äù films) and Tyler Nelson (‚ÄúRememory‚Äù); Oscar-winning VFX supervisor Dan Lemmon (‚ÄúThe Jungle Book‚Äù); Oscar-nominated SFX supervisor Dominic Tuohy (‚Äú1917,‚Äù ‚ÄúStar Wars: Episode IX ‚Äì The Rise of Skywalker‚Äù); Oscar-nominated sound mixer Stuart Wilson (‚Äú1917,‚Äù the ‚ÄúStar Wars‚Äù franchise); Oscar-winning costume designer Jacqueline Durran (‚Äú1917,‚Äù ‚ÄúLittle Women,‚Äù ‚ÄúAnna Karenina‚Äù) and costume designers Glyn Dillon (the ‚ÄúStar Wars‚Äù franchise) and David Crossman (‚Äú1917,‚Äù the ‚ÄúStar Wars‚Äù franchise); hair designer Zoe Tahir (upcoming ‚ÄúNo Time to Die,‚Äù ‚ÄúSpectre‚Äù); and Oscar-nominated makeup designer Naomi Donne (‚Äú1917‚Äù).

Based on characters from DC.  Batman was created by Bob Kane with Bill Finger.  ‚ÄúThe Batman‚Äù is set to open in theaters October 1, 2021 in select 3D and 2D and IMAX theaters and will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures.

snippet.title: Wonder Woman 1984 - Official Main Trailer
snippet.description:
The new era of Wonder Woman begins here. #WW84 only in theaters.
 
http://www.facebook.com/WonderWomanFilm
http://twitter.com/WonderWomanFilm
http://www.instagram.com/wonderwomanfilm
http://wonderwoman1984.com
 
Fast forward to the 1980s as Wonder Woman‚Äôs next big screen adventure finds her facing two all-new foes: Max Lord and The Cheetah.  
 
With director Patty Jenkins back at the helm and Gal Gadot returning in the title role, ‚ÄúWonder Woman 1984‚Äù is Warner Bros. Pictures‚Äô follow up to the DC Super Hero‚Äôs first outing, 2017‚Äôs record-breaking ‚ÄúWonder Woman,‚Äù which took in $822 million at the worldwide box office.  The film also stars Chris Pine as Steve Trevor, Kristen Wiig as The Cheetah, Pedro Pascal as Max Lord, Robin Wright as Antiope, and Connie Nielsen as Hippolyta.
 
Charles Roven, Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Patty Jenkins, Gal Gadot and Stephen Jones are producing the film.  Rebecca Steel Roven Oakley, Richard Suckle, Marianne Jenkins, Geoff Johns, Walter Hamada, Chantal Nong Vo and Wesley Coller are the executive producers.
 
Patty Jenkins directed from a screenplay she wrote with Geoff Johns & David Callaham, story by Jenkins & Johns, based on characters from DC.  Joining the director behind the scenes are several members of her ‚ÄúWonder Woman‚Äù team, including director of photography Matthew Jensen, Oscar-nominated production designer Aline Bonetto (‚ÄúAm√©lie‚Äù), and Oscar-winning costume designer Lindy Hemming (‚ÄúTopsy-Turvy‚Äù).  Oscar-nominated editor Richard Pearson (‚ÄúUnited 93‚Äù) is cutting the film.  The music is by Oscar-winning composer Hans Zimmer (‚ÄúDunkirk,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Lion King‚Äù).
 
Warner Bros. Pictures Presents an Atlas Entertainment/Stone Quarry Production, a Patty Jenkins Film, ‚ÄúWonder Woman 1984.‚Äù  Set to open in theaters in 2D and 3D in select theaters and IMAX, it will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures.
 
This film is rated PG-13 for sequences of action and violence.

Patty Jenkins directed from a screenplay she wrote with Geoff Johns & David Callaham, story by Jenkins & Johns, based on characters from DC.  Joining the director behind the scenes are several members of her ‚ÄúWonder Woman‚Äù team, including director of photography Matthew Jensen, Oscar-nominated production designer Aline Bonetto (‚ÄúAm√©lie‚Äù), and Oscar-winning costume designer Lindy Hemming (‚ÄúTopsy-Turvy‚Äù).  Oscar-nominated editor Richard Pearson (‚ÄúUnited 93‚Äù) is cutting the film.  The music is by Oscar-winning composer Hans Zimmer (‚ÄúDunkirk,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Lion King‚Äù).
 
Warner Bros. Pictures Presents an Atlas Entertainment/Stone Quarry Production, a Patty Jenkins Film, ‚ÄúWonder Woman 1984.‚Äù  Set to open in theaters in 2D and 3D in select theaters and IMAX, it will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures.
 
This film is rated PG-13 for sequences of action and violence.

snippet.title: 'Black Panther' Star Chadwick Boseman Dies Of Cancer At Age 43
snippet.description: Actor Chadwick Boseman, known for his portrayals of Black icons Jackie Robinson and James Baldwin as well as superhero Black Panther in the Marvel Cinematic Universe, died Friday after a four-year battle with cancer. He was 43.

snippet.title: Arsenal vs Liverpool | Key Moments | Community Shield 2020
snippet.description:
Heads Up FA Cup Final winners Arsenal beat Premier League champions Liverpool on penalties to win the Community Shield, after Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang and Takumi Minamino scored for their teams. 

Follow @EmiratesFACup on Twitter for in-game highlights and match updates!

snippet.title: Wonder Woman 1984 - Official Main Trailer
snippet.description:
The new era of Wonder Woman begins here. #WW84 only in theaters.
 
http://www.facebook.com/WonderWomanFilm
http://twitter.com/WonderWomanFilm
http://www.instagram.com/wonderwomanfilm
http://wonderwoman1984.com
 
Fast forward to the 1980s as Wonder Woman‚Äôs next big screen adventure finds her facing two all-new foes: Max Lord and The Cheetah.  
 
With director Patty Jenkins back at the helm and Gal Gadot returning in the title role, ‚ÄúWonder Woman 1984‚Äù is Warner Bros. Pictures‚Äô follow up to the DC Super Hero‚Äôs first outing, 2017‚Äôs record-breaking ‚ÄúWonder Woman,‚Äù which took in $822 million at the worldwide box office.  The film also stars Chris Pine as Steve Trevor, Kristen Wiig as The Cheetah, Pedro Pascal as Max Lord, Robin Wright as Antiope, and Connie Nielsen as Hippolyta.
 
Charles Roven, Deborah Snyder, Zack Snyder, Patty Jenkins, Gal Gadot and Stephen Jones are producing the film.  Rebecca Steel Roven Oakley, Richard Suckle, Marianne Jenkins, Geoff Johns, Walter Hamada, Chantal Nong Vo and Wesley Coller are the executive producers.
 
Patty Jenkins directed from a screenplay she wrote with Geoff Johns & David Callaham, story by Jenkins & Johns, based on characters from DC.  Joining the director behind the scenes are several members of her ‚ÄúWonder Woman‚Äù team, including director of photography Matthew Jensen, Oscar-nominated production designer Aline Bonetto (‚ÄúAm√©lie‚Äù), and Oscar-winning costume designer Lindy Hemming (‚ÄúTopsy-Turvy‚Äù).  Oscar-nominated editor Richard Pearson (‚ÄúUnited 93‚Äù) is cutting the film.  The music is by Oscar-winning composer Hans Zimmer (‚ÄúDunkirk,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Lion King‚Äù).
 
Warner Bros. Pictures Presents an Atlas Entertainment/Stone Quarry Production, a Patty Jenkins Film, ‚ÄúWonder Woman 1984.‚Äù  Set to open in theaters in 2D and 3D in select theaters and IMAX, it will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures.
 
This film is rated PG-13 for sequences of action and violence.

snippet.title: Israel Adesanya, Paulo Costa get HEATED in interview before UFC 253 fight | SportsCenter
snippet.description:
UFC middleweight champion Israel Adesanya and Paulo Costa chat with Michael Eaves on SportsCenter weeks before their scheduled fight at UFC 253. Both fighters discuss their preparations in the time of COVID-19, how it has affected their families and if their schedules are getting changed at all. They then get heated, calling each other "weak," "dumb" and much more.

snippet.title: Dance Moms vs Extreme Acrobats - Insane Boys vs Girls Challenge | ft Abby Lee Miller
snippet.description:
Dance Moms Lilly and Ellie challenge two incredible gymnasts to an epic game of Boys vs Girls with Abby Lee Miller as the judge. 

THANK YOU FOR 5M!! ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è I‚Äôd like to thank each of you personally, so I‚Äôm doing a 24 hour open Zoom Sept 12&13 with surprise guests throughout! The Zoom will start at 11am EST on Sept 12, and I will share the link on my community page that morning. Make sure to subscribe and hit that bell so you'll get the post notification. 

TEXT ME: 917-540-3280

LIMITED BACK TO SCHOOL MERCH! ONE WEEK ONLY: https://shopjordanmatter.com

Many of my most popular videos feature Jack, Sol, Lilly, Ellie and Abby, but this is the first time they are all together in the same video!!! This is an epic Boys vs Girls photo challenge, and the loser has to recreate the winner's photos. We run around Santa Monica Beach all day, and I give each team the craziest challenges I can imagine. Wait until you see what I made them do- acrobatics, gymnastics, contortion, dance, flips and even a TikTok! At the end, Abby Lee Miller choreographs the final challenge and then picks the winner! If you like this video, you're going to love "Sofie Dossi vs Insane Gymnasts - Ultimate Contortion and Acro Dares" https://youtu.be/MzcBwCmS_tc

snippet.title: New Zealand PM's PERFECT Response To Trump Attacks
snippet.description:
Trump attacked New Zealand, the Prime Minister's response was perfect. Ana Kasparian and Cenk Uygur discuss on The Young Turks. Keep Hope (and TYT) Alive: http://tyt.com/go

Read more here: https://www.npr.org/sections/coronavirus-live-updates/2020/08/18/903480195/trumps-claim-of-a-new-zealand-surge-is-patently-wrong-ardern-says

"New Zealand's Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern says President Trump's claim that New Zealand now has a "big surge" in coronavirus cases is "patently wrong," adding that the two countries are not comparable in how they handle the pandemic.

"We are still one of the best-performing countries in the world when it comes to COVID," Ardern said on Tuesday. "Our workers are focused on keeping it that way."

Trump's remarks came on Monday ‚Äî the same day New Zealand reported nine new cases, and the U.S. added nearly 42,000. But the U.S. president, speaking to supporters at an airport in Mankato, Minn., claimed New Zealand was an example of a country that had early success in fighting the outbreak, only to struggle now."* 

Hosts: Ana Kasparian, Cenk Uygur

Cast: Ana Kasparian, Cenk Uygur

snippet.title: COVID-19 NZ alert level announcement from Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern | Newshub
snippet.description:
Jacinda Ardern has announced Auckland will stay in COVID-19 alert level 3 until 11:59pm on Sunday, August 30. The rest of New Zealand will remain in level 2, with a review on September 6. Watch the Prime Minister's full news conference alongside Director-General of Health Dr Ashley Bloomfield.

See more: https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/politics/2020/08/covid-19-alert-level-decision-auckland-to-remain-at-level-3-until-11-59pm-on-sunday-august-30.html

snippet.title: Losing Again: Trump's Postal Plot Backfires Amidst Bezos Feud | The Beat With Ari Melber | MSNBC
snippet.description:
Pres. Trump‚Äôs alleged efforts to subvert the Post Office for his own political agenda go beyond the current scandal over voting by mail. MSNBC‚Äôs Ari Melber reports on a long-running feud with billionaire Washington Post owner Jeff Bezos, including incriminating secret White House meetings reported by the Washington Post itself, and why the scandal matters now amidst allegations of election impropriety and the Postmaster General facing Congress, in a new installment of The Beat‚Äôs special Backstory series. snippet.title: Billie Eilish: Tiny Desk (Home) Concert
snippet.description:
The Tiny Desk is working from home for the foreseeable future. Introducing NPR Music's Tiny Desk (home) concerts, bringing you performances from across the country and the world. It's the same spirit ‚Äî stripped-down sets, an intimate setting ‚Äî just a different space.

Aug. 26, 2020 | Stephen Thompson -- It didn't take long for Billie Eilish to become one of the biggest pop stars in the world, sweep the Grammy Awards' major categories and release the latest James Bond theme. And today, at just 18, she and her brother, Finneas, have accomplished what no one has been able to do for five and a half months: perform a Tiny Desk concert in what certainly appears to be the NPR Music offices.

Of course, due to safety concerns, even the NPR Music staff can't set foot in the building that houses Bob Boilen's desk. But if you look over Eilish's shoulder, there's no mistaking the signs that she's appearing at the Tiny Desk in its present-day form: On the last day before staff began working from home, I took home the Green Bay Packers helmet that sat on the top shelf ‚Äî the one Harry Styles had signed a few weeks earlier ‚Äî for safe keeping. In this performance, that spot is empty.

So how the heck did they do it?

Honestly, it's best that you watch the whole video to experience the extent of the technical feat ‚Äî which, in the spirit of Eilish's Saturday Night Live performance, they're willing to share with you. And thankfully, we still have our ways of photographing the desk, even if the room has fallen silent.

So settle in for a welcome jolt of Tiny Desk innovation, not to mention two of the excellent standalone singles Billie Eilish has released in the past year: "my future" and "everything i wanted." And, seriously, be sure to watch until the very end.

SET LIST
"my future"
"everything i wanted"

MUSICIANS
Billie Eilish: vocals, keys; Finneas: keys, guitar

CREDITS
Video by: Matty Vogel; Audio by: Finneas; Art Director: Henry Hickman; Producer: Bob Boilen; Audio Mastering Engineer: Josh Rogosin; Video Producer: Morgan Noelle Smith; Associate Producer: Bobby Carter; Photographer: Michael Cullen; Executive Producer: Lauren Onkey; Senior VP, Programming: Anya Grundmann

At√© eu chegar, aquele grito todo, aquela gritaria toda, no terceiro andar, aquele alvoro√ßo todo, at√© a minha chegada, foi o momento em que eles j√° tinham socorrido o meu marido", a deputada justificou ao ser indagada por n√£o ter ajudado no socorro ao marido, que havia sido baleado por 30 tiros.

Animation: Falk (https://www.couchkartoffelsalat.de)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Zu Ralph Ruthe:

Ralph Ruthe ist Autor, Musiker, Filmemacher und Cartoonist.
Bereits mit 14 Jahren arbeitete Ruthe als Texter f√ºr professionelle Comic-Studios und wurde bald einer der Hauptautoren f√ºr K√§pt'n Blaub√§r. Nach seinem Zivildienst ver√∂ffentlichte er sein erstes Buch.
1998 begann Ruthe f√ºr das MAD-Magazin zu arbeiten, und wurde einer der beliebtesten Zeichner und Autoren.
Seit 2003 konzentriert er sich auf seine Cartoonserie SHIT HAPPENS!, die in vielen Zeitungen und Magazinen in ganz Europa erscheinen. Au√üerdem arbeitet er regelm√§√üig an seiner Serie FR√úHREIF, die f√ºr eine TV-Umsetzung bearbeitet wurde. 
Von 2005 bis 2008 erhielt er viermal hintereinander f√ºr SHIT HAPPENS den Sondermann-Preis der Frankfurter Buchmesse in der Kategorie "Cartoon". 2008 und 2009 gewann der den 1. Preis beim Berliner Kurzfilmfestival "Going Underground".
Mit seiner Multimedia-Comedy-Liveshow tritt er deutschlandweit in ausverkauften Theatern auf.
